history.content: Math 54's workload is not bad at all and the concepts are not terribly difficult. The greatest consideration is how fast are you comfortable learning at. Two technicals is a large workload though doable with the right attitude. You would need to be very careful about not falling behind

How manageable would it be if I were to take EE 40 and Math 54 over the summer? Is it very time-consuming or difficult to do so? The reason behind EE 40 is that I want to take it before it is replaced as a requirement by the EE 16A/B series. I've heard mixed responses about that combination of classes for the summer.
